# Code Review Checklist

This checklist defines quality standards for AI code review, aligned with enterprise Spring Boot and Next.js best practices.

## 1. Architecture Compliance

### Backend Services (Spring Boot)

#### Clean Layering (AD-002)
- [ ] Controllers only handle HTTP concerns (validation, response mapping)
- [ ] Services contain business logic, transactions
- [ ] Repositories only contain data access (no business logic)
- [ ] No repository calls in controllers
- [ ] No business logic in repositories
- [ ] DTOs used for API contracts, separate from domain entities

#### Dependency Direction (AD-003)
- [ ] Controller → Service → Repository (correct)
- [ ] No circular dependencies between layers
- [ ] Shared-lib dependencies flow correctly

#### Service Boundaries (AD-004)
- [ ] auth-service: Authentication, authorization, user management only
- [ ] crm-service: CRM domain logic only (leads, opportunities, accounts)
- [ ] api-gateway: Routing, rate limiting, authentication delegation only
- [ ] No direct database calls between services
- [ ] Inter-service communication via OpenFeign or events

### Frontend (Next.js/React)

#### Feature-Based Structure
- [ ] Features organized in `app/[feature]` folders
- [ ] Shared components in `components/` with clear purpose
- [ ] Business logic in custom hooks or Zustand stores
- [ ] API calls centralized in `services/api/`

#### Component Design
- [ ] Components <200 lines (extract if larger)
- [ ] Single Responsibility Principle
- [ ] Props interface properly typed
- [ ] No prop drilling (use context or Zustand for deep state)

## 2. Code Quality Standards

### Zero Warnings Policy (MANDATORY)

#### Backend (Java/Maven)
- [ ] **ZERO compiler warnings** - Build must pass with `-Werror`
- [ ] No unchecked warnings (`@SuppressWarnings` only with justification)
- [ ] No raw types (use generics properly: `List<String>` not `List`)
- [ ] No deprecated API usage (migrate to current APIs)
- [ ] No unused imports or variables
- [ ] No unnecessary casts
- [ ] No empty catch/try/finally blocks
- [ ] No switch fallthrough without comment
- [ ] Fix all IDE warnings (IntelliJ IDEA inspections)

**Enforced by:**
- Maven compiler plugin with `-Xlint:all -Werror`
- Pre-commit hook: `mvn compile` must succeed
- CI Pipeline: Build fails on warnings

**Suppressing Warnings (Rare Cases Only):**
```java
// ✅ GOOD: Justified suppression with explanation
@SuppressWarnings("unchecked") // Safe: We control the cache type
private <T> T getFromCache(String key) {
    return (T) cache.get(key);
}

// ❌ BAD: Blanket suppression without reason
@SuppressWarnings("all")
public void someMethod() { ... }
```

#### Frontend (TypeScript/ESLint)
- [ ] **ZERO ESLint warnings** - Only errors or clean
- [ ] No `@ts-ignore` without explanation
- [ ] No `any` type without justification
- [ ] No unused variables or imports
- [ ] No console.log in production code
- [ ] Fix all TypeScript strict mode issues

**Enforced by:**
- ESLint configuration with `max-warnings: 0`
- Pre-commit hook: `npm run lint` must pass
- CI Pipeline: Lint fails on warnings

### Null Safety (AD-006)

#### Backend (Java)
- [ ] Use `Optional<T>` for nullable returns
- [ ] Never return null from service methods
- [ ] Use `Objects.requireNonNull()` for critical parameters
- [ ] `@NotNull`, `@NotBlank` on DTO fields
- [ ] Constructor parameters validated or final
- [ ] No `Optional.get()` without `isPresent()` check

#### Frontend (TypeScript)
- [ ] Use `?.` optional chaining
- [ ] Use `??` nullish coalescing
- [ ] Properly typed (no `any` except in controlled cases)
- [ ] Guard clauses for nullable values

### Error Handling (AD-007)

#### Backend
- [ ] All errors use `ErrorCode` enum (no raw strings)
- [ ] Business errors throw `BusinessException`
- [ ] Validation errors throw `ValidationException`
- [ ] No empty catch blocks
- [ ] No generic `Exception` catches (use specific types)
- [ ] Errors logged with context (traceId, userId, errorCode)
- [ ] Never expose stack traces in API responses

#### Frontend
- [ ] Use `parseApiError()` for API errors
- [ ] Display user-friendly messages (not raw error codes)
- [ ] Handle loading/error states in all queries/mutations
- [ ] Error boundaries for component trees
- [ ] Log errors to monitoring (if configured)

### Transaction Management (AD-008)

#### Backend Only
- [ ] `@Transactional` on service methods that modify data
- [ ] Read-only transactions: `@Transactional(readOnly = true)`
- [ ] Proper isolation level (default REPEATABLE_READ is usually correct)
- [ ] No long-running transactions (>5 seconds)
- [ ] Transactions don't span HTTP calls or external I/O
- [ ] Rollback on business exceptions: `@Transactional(rollbackFor = BusinessException.class)`

### Input Validation

#### Backend
- [ ] All DTOs have `@Valid` annotation
- [ ] Required fields: `@NotNull`, `@NotBlank`
- [ ] String length: `@Size(min=, max=)`
- [ ] Email format: `@Email`
- [ ] Custom validation: `@Pattern`, custom validators
- [ ] Validate enums (no raw strings)
- [ ] Sanitize user input for SQL/XSS

#### Frontend
- [ ] All forms use `react-hook-form` + `zod`
- [ ] Zod schemas for validation
- [ ] Client-side validation before API call
- [ ] Display field-level errors
- [ ] Disable submit during validation

### Naming Conventions

#### Backend
- [ ] Classes: PascalCase (UserService, AccountRepository)
- [ ] Methods: camelCase (getUserById, createLead)
- [ ] Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (MAX_RETRY_ATTEMPTS)
- [ ] Packages: lowercase (com.company.platform.auth)
- [ ] REST endpoints: kebab-case (/api/users/profile, /api/leads/active)
- [ ] Database tables: snake_case (auth_user, crm_lead)

#### Frontend
- [ ] Components: PascalCase (UserProfile, LeadForm)
- [ ] Functions: camelCase (getUserById, formatDate)
- [ ] Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (API_BASE_URL)
- [ ] CSS classes: kebab-case (user-profile, lead-form)
- [ ] Files: kebab-case (user-profile.tsx, lead-form.tsx)

### Code Smells

#### General
- [ ] No methods >50 lines (extract sub-methods)
- [ ] No classes >500 lines (split responsibilities)
- [ ] No duplicated logic (extract to shared utility)
- [ ] No magic numbers (use named constants)
- [ ] No commented-out code (remove or document why)
- [ ] No TODOs without ticket references

#### Backend-Specific
- [ ] No God classes (services with >15 public methods)
- [ ] No anemic domain models (entities with only getters/setters)
- [ ] No static utility classes with state
- [ ] No Lombok `@Data` (use `@Getter`, `@Builder` explicitly)

#### Frontend-Specific
- [ ] No inline styles (use Tailwind classes)
- [ ] No hardcoded strings (use i18n)
- [ ] No useEffect with missing dependencies
- [ ] No unnecessary re-renders (use React.memo, useMemo)

## 3. Security Standards

### Authentication & Authorization (AD-009)

#### Backend
- [ ] All endpoints have `@PreAuthorize` or `@Secured` (except public health checks)
- [ ] Role checks use `hasRole('ROLE_ADMIN')` format
- [ ] JWT tokens validated on every request
- [ ] Refresh tokens stored securely
- [ ] Passwords hashed with BCrypt (min strength 12)
- [ ] Sensitive fields use `@JsonIgnore`
- [ ] Session timeout configured (30 minutes default)

#### Frontend
- [ ] Auth tokens stored in httpOnly cookies (not localStorage)
- [ ] Redirect to login if 401 response
- [ ] Protected routes check auth state
- [ ] Hide UI elements based on user roles
- [ ] Logout clears all auth state

### Input Sanitization

#### Backend
- [ ] No raw SQL queries (use JPQL or Criteria API)
- [ ] Parameterized queries only (prevent SQL injection)
- [ ] File uploads validate type and size
- [ ] Path traversal protection (validate file paths)
- [ ] No reflection on user input
- [ ] Deserialize only trusted classes

#### Frontend
- [ ] Escape user content before rendering
- [ ] Use `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` only when necessary (and sanitize)
- [ ] Validate URLs before navigation
- [ ] CSRF tokens in forms
- [ ] No eval() or Function() constructor

### Secrets Management

#### Backend
- [ ] No hardcoded credentials
- [ ] Use environment variables for secrets
- [ ] Encrypt sensitive data at rest
- [ ] Log statements don't include passwords/tokens
- [ ] API keys rotated regularly

#### Frontend
- [ ] No API keys in client code
- [ ] Use backend proxy for third-party APIs
- [ ] No sensitive data in URL params
- [ ] No sensitive data in localStorage

### CORS & CSP

#### Backend
- [ ] CORS configured (no `allowedOrigins = "*"` in production)
- [ ] Allowed origins whitelist
- [ ] Credentials allowed only for trusted origins

#### Frontend
- [ ] CSP headers configured
- [ ] Only load resources from trusted domains

## 4. Database Performance (AD-010)

### Query Optimization

#### Backend Only
- [ ] No N+1 queries (use `@EntityGraph` or `JOIN FETCH`)
- [ ] Pagination for list endpoints (`Pageable` parameter)
- [ ] Indexes on foreign keys
- [ ] Indexes on frequently queried fields
- [ ] Avoid `SELECT *` (fetch only needed columns)
- [ ] Use projections for read-heavy queries
- [ ] Batch inserts/updates (use `saveAll()`, not loops)

### Connection Management
- [ ] Connection pool sized correctly (10-20 for small apps)
- [ ] Timeouts configured (30s max)
- [ ] No long-running transactions
- [ ] Close resources in finally blocks or try-with-resources

### Caching Strategy
- [ ] Read-heavy data cached (e.g., lookup tables)
- [ ] Cache eviction strategy defined
- [ ] Cache keys include tenant/user context
- [ ] No caching of sensitive data

## 5. Observability (AD-011)

### Logging Standards

#### Backend
- [ ] Structured JSON logging (use logback-spring.xml)
- [ ] Log level appropriate:
  - ERROR: System failures
  - WARN: Business exceptions, degraded performance
  - INFO: Normal business operations
  - DEBUG: Diagnostic info (not in production)
- [ ] Include context: `log.info("User logged in: userId={}", userId)`
- [ ] No sensitive data in logs (passwords, tokens, PII)
- [ ] Log all exceptions with stack trace
- [ ] TraceId included in all log statements

#### Frontend
- [ ] Console logs removed in production build
- [ ] Errors sent to monitoring service
- [ ] User actions logged for analytics (if required)

### Metrics
- [ ] Expose `/actuator/prometheus` endpoint
- [ ] Custom metrics for business operations (registrations, orders)
- [ ] Track API response times
- [ ] Track error rates by endpoint

### Tracing
- [ ] TraceId propagated across services
- [ ] Spans created for service methods
- [ ] TraceId included in error responses

## 6. Testing Standards

### Backend Tests

#### Unit Tests
- [ ] Service methods have unit tests
- [ ] Mock repositories (use Mockito)
- [ ] Test happy path + edge cases
- [ ] Test exception scenarios
- [ ] Assert specific exceptions (not just `assertThrows`)

#### Integration Tests
- [ ] Repository tests use `@DataJpaTest`
- [ ] Controller tests use `@WebMvcTest`
- [ ] Test full request/response cycle
- [ ] Test validation failures
- [ ] Test authorization (403 responses)

#### Coverage Targets
- [ ] Line coverage: ≥80%
- [ ] Branch coverage: ≥75%
- [ ] Exclude generated code, DTOs, configs from coverage

### Frontend Tests

#### Component Tests
- [ ] Render tests for all components
- [ ] User interaction tests (click, type, submit)
- [ ] Loading state tests
- [ ] Error state tests
- [ ] Mock API calls (use MSW)

#### Hook Tests
- [ ] Test custom hooks with `renderHook`
- [ ] Test state changes
- [ ] Test side effects

#### Coverage Targets
- [ ] Line coverage: ≥75%
- [ ] Branch coverage: ≥70%
- [ ] Function coverage: ≥70%
- [ ] Statement coverage: ≥70%

### Test Quality
- [ ] Tests are independent (no shared state)
- [ ] Tests have clear arrange/act/assert structure
- [ ] Test names describe behavior (not implementation)
- [ ] No flaky tests (fix or skip)
- [ ] Fast tests (<1s per unit test)

## 7. Performance Standards

### Backend Performance

#### API Response Times
- [ ] GET requests: <200ms (p95)
- [ ] POST/PUT/DELETE: <500ms (p95)
- [ ] Bulk operations: <2s (p95)

#### Optimization Techniques
- [ ] Use database indexes
- [ ] Lazy load collections
- [ ] Paginate large results
- [ ] Cache frequently accessed data
- [ ] Use projections for large entities
- [ ] Batch database operations

### Frontend Performance

#### Bundle Size
- [ ] Total bundle: <500KB gzipped
- [ ] Code splitting for large features
- [ ] Tree-shaking enabled
- [ ] Remove unused dependencies

#### Rendering Performance
- [ ] Use React.memo for expensive components
- [ ] Use useMemo for expensive calculations
- [ ] Use useCallback for event handlers in lists
- [ ] Virtualize long lists (react-window)
- [ ] Optimize images (next/image)

#### Network Performance
- [ ] Prefetch critical data
- [ ] Debounce search inputs
- [ ] Cache API responses (TanStack Query)
- [ ] Compress API responses

## 8. Internationalization (i18n)

### Backend
- [ ] Error messages use MessageService
- [ ] Accept-Language header respected
- [ ] Locale fallback to English
- [ ] No hardcoded user-facing strings

### Frontend
- [ ] All text uses `useTranslations` hook
- [ ] Translation keys follow convention (errors.USER_100)
- [ ] Locale switcher works
- [ ] Date/time formatted per locale
- [ ] Number/currency formatted per locale

## 9. Accessibility (Frontend Only)

- [ ] Semantic HTML (header, nav, main, footer)
- [ ] ARIA labels on interactive elements
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works
- [ ] Focus indicators visible
- [ ] Color contrast ≥4.5:1
- [ ] Form errors announced to screen readers
- [ ] Images have alt text

## 10. Git & Documentation

### Commit Standards
- [ ] Commit message includes Feature ID (e.g., CRM-015)
- [ ] Commit message format: `type: description` (feat, fix, refactor, test, docs)
- [ ] Commits are atomic (one logical change per commit)

### Documentation
- [ ] Public APIs have JavaDoc/TSDoc
- [ ] Complex logic has explanatory comments
- [ ] README updated if public interface changed
- [ ] Architecture Decision Records (ADRs) updated if architecture changed

